        "Klobuchar": null,
        "Warren": null
      },
      "mechanic_quote": "the other candidates' plans would replace a caregiver's earnings in the Social Security benefit formula with the caregiver credit as long as that credit exceeded the worker's earnings (printed p. 11)",
      "biden_variant_note": "Biden's statutory design provides the credit on top of earnings and phases it out 50 cents per $1 earned; the registration models all four plans with the uniform top-up-to-credit-level mechanic, so Biden's phase-out is not separately encoded (a named simplification)."
    },
    "table15_bottom_fifth_2065": {
      "citation": "Table 15 (Percentage of Benefit Increases Going to the Bottom Fifth of Lifetime Earners, 2065), printed p. 66, 'Create caregiver credit' row, scheduled scenario; DYNASIM3 ID980",
